	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dual wield skill is definitely dictated by the delay of the OFFHAND weapon.  If it weren't, there would be no way that my warrior could swing his 18 delay offhand weapon 4 times before his primary (a 25/40 wurmslayer) cycles.  Going by your theory, any offhand weapon I use would be downgraded to a 40 delay to match my wurmslayer, and that simply isn't the case.  Also, if it were dictated by main hand delay, wouldn't everyone's offhand weapon swing at exactly the same time as the main hand if the main hand weapon was slower?  That certainly isn't the case either.  I've used a wurmslayer for over 20 levels, and my offhand weapons all work on their own separate delay.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
