	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is correct, in that offhand delay does in fact matter as to when your second weapon attacks, BUT since you do not get a damage bonus to your offhand weapon, most folks prefer a weapon with a little more oomph to it.  At higher levels, a lower delay is a bit more preferable for most melees for their main hand weapon than a bit extra base damage, cause you can be doing 10, 15 bonus damage per swing twice as often than 2 or 4 more base damage half as often.  This does not apply to secondary melee slot.  Hence the reason the Mosscovered Twig went from Uber to Crap in one swell foop when they made it offhand only.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
