	   <tr><td colspan=2>Probably the main reason to not use a piercing weapon in off hand is the fact that high damage piercing weapons are very hard to acquire.  Obviously, this is due to how backstab damage is calculated.<br><br>The highest damage rogue useable piercing weapon available in the game has a damage of 15.  If you can finda  1HS or 1HB with a better damage and comparable delay, go ahead and put it into the off hand.  You're not going to be backstabbing with that.  It makes it even better if you can find one that procs something useful or has decent stats on it.  All in all, it really doesn't matter _that_ much whether you use piercing, 1HS, or 1HB in off hand...just use the best weapon you can find there.  Yes, I know that for rogue, piercing skil maxes higher than either of the others, but I'm really not sure if it makes so much difference that you should sacrifice a higher dmg other type weapon to use a piercer because you have a higher piercing skill.<br><br>Any other ideas?<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
